body:
I agree. This "Don't call reset inside onSubmit" is quite strange since it is a very common pattern to reset a form after it is submitted. 

Even the docs themselves break this rule: 
https://react-hook-form.com/advanced-usage#TestingForm
```tsx
...
const onSubmit = async data => {
    await login(data.email, data.password);
    reset();
  };
...
```
